['text':'!/bin/bash','line_number':1,'multiline':False]['text':' Subsetting DejaVu fonts to create a display-math-only font','line_number':3,'multiline':False]['text':' The DejaVu fonts include math display variants outside of the Unicode range,','line_number':5,'multiline':False]['text':' and it is currently hard to access them from matplotlib. The subset.py script','line_number':6,'multiline':False]['text':' in `tools` has been modified to move the math display variants found in DejaVu','line_number':7,'multiline':False]['text':' fonts into a new TTF font with these variants in the Unicode range.','line_number':8,'multiline':False]['text':' This bash script calls the subset.py scripts with the appropriate options to','line_number':10,'multiline':False]['text':' generate the new font files `DejaVuSansDisplay.ttf` and','line_number':11,'multiline':False]['text':' `DejaVuSerifDisplay.ttf`:','line_number':12,'multiline':False]['text':' test that fontforge is installed','line_number':16,'multiline':False]